result.adr_address: 23 Mosque St, Central, Mid-Levels, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 23 Mosque St, Central, Mid-Levels, Hong Kong
result.name: Pizzeria Italia

reviews.text:
A Pizzeria Italia was opened by an Italian chef in Mosque Street more than 20 yrs ago.  The pizzas were of thin crust Italian style and very delicious. However it closed down about 7 to 8 years ago.
Currently there are 2 Pizzeria Italia resurrected in HK, in High Street and again Mosque Street reapectively.
Visited the Mosque St branch tonight.
The pizzas are good & of the same style as before and the pork ribs excellent.
Prices resonable.
Staff were friendly and helpful.
Will go back for sure!

Bad customer service. Tried to call to order pizza for the past 20 min and no one picked up. When i call their other shop on high street to ask if there's other number i can reach them. The other shop just went no other number and hung up on me, doesn't seem to care at all that other shop is unreachable for their customers.
Pizza was simply average, many better places in Hong Kong! Service was bad and many food delivery guys are hanging around in front of the restaurant. Terrible ambience. Will not go back.

Pizza is good, but service is real bad. I ordered a pizza to take out and wait for 30 minutes and the pizza is still 'in the oven'. Funny thing is that I kept seeing fresh pizza coming out, for customers order after me. 4 star pizza, 1 star service.
Super friendly staff and best pizza in Hong Kong!
